        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">based on annual production volume of sodium hydroxide, namely 1.03E+10 kg in 2022 (mathematical relation in chlor alkali electrolysis).

The amount of sodium hydroxide used as neutralising agent is based on statistics of the DOW chemical company on its uses in 2002. 18% of NaOH is used in the paper and pulp industries. 5% is used in water treatment. It is assumed that all neutralising agent applications are in these 2 sectors. This assumption is based on a market research by Marianne Wesnæs and Bo Weidema, 2.-0 LCA consultants, www.lca-net.com, 2006-10-19. URL: http://www.lca-net.com/files/naoh.pdf  Retrieved 13.02.2012</productionVolumeComment>
